The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Beijing, June 19: China today announced it would take steps to let the yuan appreciate against the US dollar in tandem with a demand for the same from America. The Chinese central bank today said it would proceed further with the reform of the renminbi or yuan exchange rate regime to enhance its exchange rate flexibility. The Peoples Bank of China said the decision had been made in view of developments in the financial market at home and abroad.                            
	 Calcutta, June 19: Berger Paints India today reported a 35 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 120.14 crore in 2009-10 against Rs 88.76 crore in 2008-09. Consolidated net profit rose 45 per cent to Rs 120.39 crore in 2009-10.                                                                                                                          
